\n   - `xl` → 4500s (75 min)\n3. Capability multiplier applied on top of effort base: `simple` ×1.0, `moderate` ×1.25, `complex` ×1.5. When `capability` is `trivial` or missing, use ×1.0.\n4. Resolution order (highest priority wins):\n   - `cli_override` (integer minutes, if provided)\n   - PRD frontmatter `timeout_minutes` field (integer minutes)\n   - Config table lookup (`[timeouts]` section in `.darkfactory/config.toml`) by effort × capability multiplier\n   - Built-in defaults × capability multiplier\n5. The function returns an integer (seconds) and a string describing the source (e.g. `\"cli\"`, `\"prd_frontmatter\"`, `\"config\"`, `\"default\"`).\n6. Add a `[timeouts]` section to `.darkfactory/config.toml` schema with keys for each effort tier (values in minutes) and capability multipliers.\n7. If the PRD has no `effort` field, fall back to `s` (10 min) as the default.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/timeouts.py`\n\n```python\nDEFAULT_EFFORT_TIMEOUTS = {\n    \"xs\": 300,\n    \"s\": 600,\n    \"m\": 1200,\n    \"l\": 2400,\n    \"xl\": 4500,\n}\n\nCAPABILITY_MULTIPLIERS = {\n    \"trivial\": 1.0,\n    \"simple\": 1.0,\n    \"moderate\": 1.25,\n    \"complex\": 1.5,\n}\n\ndef resolve_timeout(\n    effort: str | None,\n    capability: str | None,\n    timeout_minutes_frontmatter: int | None,\n    config_timeouts: dict | None,\n    cli_override: int | None,\n) -> tuple[int, str]:\n    \"\"\"Return (timeout_seconds, source_description).\"\"\"\n    ...\n```\n\n### Config schema addition (`.darkfactory/config.toml`)\n\n```toml\n[timeouts]\nxs = 5       # minutes\ns = 10\nm = 20\nl = 40\nxl = 75\n\n[timeouts.capability_multipliers]\ntrivial = 1.0\nsimple = 1.0\nmoderate = 1.25\ncomplex = 1.5\n```\n\n### Unit tests (`tests/test_timeouts.py`)\n\nTable-driven tests covering:\n- Every effort tier with default mapping\n- Every capability multiplier\n- PRD frontmatter override takes precedence over config/defaults\n- CLI override takes precedence over everything\n- Config table overrides built-in defaults\n- Missing effort falls back to `s`\n- Missing capability uses multiplier 1.0\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `resolve_timeout()` returns correct seconds for each effort tier using built-in defaults.\n- [ ] AC-2: Capability multiplier is applied correctly on top of effort base.\n- [ ] AC-3: PRD frontmatter `timeout_minutes` overrides computed value.\n- [ ] AC-4: CLI override (minutes) overrides everything.\n- [ ] AC-5: Config table values override built-in defaults.\n- [ ] AC-6: Function returns both timeout value and source string.\n- [ ] AC-7: Unit tests cover all resolution paths with table-driven tests.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01G58idpVahkqgvouAwLMFjF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01F573zxMoEEtwGLiLw1gh7R","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-542-effort-based-agent-timeouts/prds/PRD-542.2-integrate-timeout-into-runner.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-542.2\"\ntitle: \"Integrate effort-based timeout into harness runner\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-542-effort-based-agent-timeouts]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-542.1-timeout-resolution-module]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-542.3-graceful-timeout-handling]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/runner.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n---\n\n# Integrate effort-based timeout into harness runner\n\n## Summary\n\nWire the `resolve_timeout()` function from `darkfactory/timeouts.py` into the harness runner so that agent task invocations use effort-based timeouts instead of the hardcoded 600s default. Add a `--timeout` CLI flag to `prd run` that overrides all other timeout sources. Log the resolved timeout and its source when each task starts.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. In `runner.py`'s `_run_agent()` function, call `resolve_timeout()` with the PRD's effort, capability, `timeout_minutes` frontmatter field, config timeouts, and any CLI override.\n2. Pass the resolved timeout (in seconds) to `invoke_claude()` as `timeout_seconds`.\n3. Add `--timeout <minutes>` flag to the `prd run` CLI command. This value is threaded through to `resolve_timeout()` as the CLI override.\n4. When a task starts, log a message like: `Timeout: 1200s (source: default, effort=m, capability×1.0)` so failures are diagnosable.\n5. Read timeout config from `.darkfactory/config.toml` `[timeouts]` section if present.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/runner.py`\n\nIn the `_run_agent()` method (around line 293-302), before calling `invoke_claude()`:\n\n```python\nfrom darkfactory.timeouts import resolve_timeout\n\ntimeout_seconds, timeout_source = resolve_timeout(\n    effort=prd.frontmatter.get(\"effort\"),\n    capability=prd.frontmatter.get(\"capability\"),\n    timeout_minutes_frontmatter=prd.frontmatter.get(\"timeout_minutes\"),\n    config_timeouts=self.config.get(\"timeouts\"),\n    cli_override=self.cli_timeout_minutes,\n)\nlogger.info(\"Timeout: %ds (source: %s)\", timeout_seconds, timeout_source)\n```\n\nThen pass `timeout_seconds=timeout_seconds` to `invoke_claude()`.\n\n### `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\nAdd `--timeout` option to the `prd run` command:\n\n```python\n@click.option(\"--timeout\", type=int, default=None, help=\"Override timeout in minutes\")\n```\n\nThread the value through to the runner.\n\n### Config reading\n\nIf `.darkfactory/config.toml` has a `[timeouts]` section, parse it and pass to `resolve_timeout()`. If the section doesn't exist, pass `None` (built-in defaults apply).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: Agent tasks use effort-based timeouts from `resolve_timeout()` instead of hardcoded 600s.\n- [ ] AC-2: `prd run --timeout 30` sets a 30-minute timeout that overrides all other sources.\n- [ ] AC-3: When a task starts, the log shows the resolved timeout value and source.\n- [ ] AC-4: Config timeouts from `.darkfactory/config.toml` are read and passed to `resolve_timeout()`.\n- [ ] AC-5: When no config or CLI override is present, the default effort-based mapping is used.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":477,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2982,"cache_read_input_tokens":21754,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2982},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b720c5ee-3335-470d-b4c3-b85e3ba705c0","uuid":"1207dd94-95fb-41f5-b187-c537d54495ce"}
